{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f15a74b-28f6-4cc0-93f6-61c8073a0835","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"62346da5-aadd-4d20-9415-ad55e21abfc6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test skip/ignore attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"BD0A:2DE6FB:1CFF5F2:20B1DC6:6A07C4EB"},"id":"fe4c2ed9-c6b3-4cbf-8e33-95bec82bc360","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:25.425Z","parentId":"5b6229a4-ac96-4526-89cf-24b59f664350"}
